,"1304":"1304年","1269":"1269年","1214":"1214年","before 1240":"1240年之前","1240":"1240年","1273":"1273年","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"蘇格蘭阿吉爾吉爾馬丁","Argyll, Scotland":"蘇格蘭阿吉爾","lifeSummary":"Beatrix Fraser於1216年出生在蘇格蘭阿吉爾。她於1240年之前與Reverend James Hadden在蘇格蘭阿吉爾結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。她去世於1273年在蘇格蘭阿吉爾吉爾馬丁享年57歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1216–1273":"1216年–1273年","1214–1269":"1214年–1269年","1240–1304":"1240年–1304年","1216":"1216年","1304":"1304年","1269":"1269年","1214":"1214年","before 1240":"1240年之前","1240":"1240年","1273":"1273年","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"苏格兰阿吉爾吉爾馬丁","Argyll, Scotland":"苏格兰阿吉爾","lifeSummary":"Beatrix Fraser于1216年出生在苏格兰阿吉爾。她于1240年之前与Reverend James Hadden在苏格兰阿吉爾结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。她去世于1273年在苏格兰阿吉爾吉爾馬丁享年57岁。"},"hr":{"1216–1273":"1216.–1273.","1214–1269":"1214–1269.","1240–1304":"1240.–1304","1216":"1216.","1304":"1304","1269":"1269.","1214":"1214","before 1240":"prije 1240.","1240":"1240.","1273":"1273.","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"cs":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"před 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"da":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"før 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Skotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Skotland"},"nl":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"vóór 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Schotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Schotland"},"en":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"before 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fraser","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: apparently a nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>fraser(e)</i>, <i>fresere</i> ‘strawberry plant’. <i>Fresel</i> and <i>Frisel</i>, from Anglo-Norman French <i>fresel</i> ‘strawberry’, are early variants of the Fraser surname, the modern Gaelicized form of which is <b>Friseal</b>. See   Frizzell  . The crest on the Scottish family's coat of arms takes the form of a strawberry plant, but its antiquity is unknown. Claims of a habitational derivation, in particular from a place called la Frézelière in Anjou (France), are attractive but they lack verifiable evidence.","Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Jewish surnames.","History: There are two clans Fraser in Scotland, with common ancestry going back to Simon Fraser of Keith in East Lothian, who lived in the 12th century. One of these clans has its seat at Philorth Castle (subsequently re-named Cairnbulg) on the northeast coast of Scotland. Sir Alexander Fraser, 8th laird of Philorth (<i>c.</i> 1536–1623) converted the fishing village of Faithlie into the burgh of Fraserburgh in the 1590s. The other clan is Fraser of Lovat, associated mainly with the city of Inverness are. They are descended from Simon Fraser, a younger son, who lived in the early 14th century. In Gaelic, the head of Clan Fraser of Lovat is known as <i>Mac Shimi</i> ‘son of Simon’."],"variants":[{"name":"Frayser","meanings":["Probably an altered form of   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frasier","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frasure","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frazer","meanings":["Variant of   Fraser  , associated chiefly with northern Ireland."]},{"name":"Fraizer","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frashier","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Fraiser","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frizzell","meanings":["English and Irish: nickname from Old French <i>fresel</i>, <i>frisel</i> ‘lace, ribbon, braid, brooch, frill, ruff’, for someone with an ornate style of dress, or ‘object of little value’ (a diminutive of <i>frese</i>, of ancient Germanic origin).","Scottish: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fresel</i> ‘strawberry’, an alternative form of   Fraser  ."]},{"name":"Frazier","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Fraser  .","Americanized form of French <b>Frégeau</b> (see   Fregeau  )."]},{"name":"Frasher","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Fraser  .","Possibly an altered form of German <b>Fratzscher</b> (see   Frutchey  )."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrix Fraser was born in 1216, in Argyll, Scotland. She married Reverend James Hadden before 1240, in Argyll, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1273, in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"enne 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"ennen vuotta 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"avant 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Écosse","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Beatrix Fraser est née en 1216, à Argyll, Écosse. Elle a épousé Reverend James Hadden avant 1240, à Argyll, Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1273, à Kilmartin, Argyll, Écosse, à l’âge de 57 ans."},"de":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"vor 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Beatrix Fraser wurde 1216 in Argyll, Scotland geboren. Sie hat vor 1240 in Argyll, Scotland Reverend James Hadden geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1273 im Alter von 57 Jahren in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland."},"ht":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"before 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"hu":{"1216–1273":"1216–1273","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1216":"1216","1304":"1304","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","before 1240":"1240 előtt","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Ar